rComments: Her lectures were very clear. She made sure that you knew every single step to get to where you needed to be. Very helpful. Explained in depth. Her notes were the book which you had to fill in and helped with keeping you engaged.

Very helpful about the expectations on quizzes and tests. She pushes you to cold memorize the entire unit circle, limits, & prohibits formula tables on the final, but you'll thank her in the end. Definitely a class worth taking if you want to do well in Math 220/221 and 231.
